50|$|<b>Virtual</b> <b>temperature</b> {{is used in}} {{adjusting}} CAPE soundings {{for assessing}} available convective potential energy from skew-T log-P diagrams. The errors associated with ignoring <b>virtual</b> <b>temperature</b> correction for smaller CAPE values can be quite significant. Thus, {{in the early stages}} of convective storm formation, a <b>virtual</b> <b>temperature</b> correction is significant in identifying the potential intensity in tropical cyclogenesis.|$|E
50|$|The CIN {{energy value}} is an {{important}} figure on a skew-T log-P diagram and is a helpful value in evaluating the severity of a convective event. On a skew-T log-P diagram, CIN is any area between the warmer environment <b>virtual</b> <b>temperature</b> profile and the cooler parcel <b>virtual</b> <b>temperature</b> profile.|$|E
